<p>A Paris court is expected to set on Monday when and where former French president Nicolas Sarkozy will begin serving a five-year prison sentence following his conviction for criminal conspiracy tied to alleged Libyan financing of his 2007 presidential campaign [france24.com#2][lemonde.fr#3][abcnews.go.com#4][thehindu.com#1]. Sarkozy, 70, maintains his innocence, called the verdict “a scandal,” and has filed an appeal, but authorities will proceed with imprisonment scheduling despite the appeal [france24.com#2][scmp.com#5]. He led France from 2007 to 2012, and the case marks the first time a former president of modern France faces actual time behind bars [thehindu.com#1][scmp.com#5].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/BtXjPOnnGadK3nAYZn3Z4UGOZRjhtK8vMklM3zczYedUIMMiAUOCR0cK0mFJVyEmz4oxbdp6KtitSGnVBBC75G5o3YswVJWDkNA5il8WCmbILmGjPLdK64ZdpKc33jgdp_sVKHWojl0qGRYg7QZQBAdGbrI_c7p9PxFfrJx7gQ' alt='Former French president Nicolas Sarkozy.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>What happens: A Paris court will determine the start date and location for Sarkozy to serve his sentence on Monday [france24.com#2][lemonde.fr#3][abcnews.go.com#4].</li><li>Case background: Sarkozy was convicted in late September of criminal conspiracy over a scheme involving alleged Libyan funding of his 2007 campaign under Moamer Kadhafi [thehindu.com#1][france24.com#2].</li><li>Appeal filed: He denounced the verdict as “a scandal” and appealed, yet the imprisonment scheduling moves forward [france24.com#2][scmp.com#5].</li><li>Sentence length: The court-imposed sentence is five years of imprisonment [france24.com#2][scmp.com#5].</li><li>Historical note: He is the first former president of modern France sentenced to actual time behind bars [scmp.com#5].</li></ul><blockquote>A scandal - Nicolas Sarkozy</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Nicolas Sarkozy: He denies wrongdoing, calls the verdict “a scandal,” and has appealed the ruling. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/france/20251013-france-ex-president-sarkozy-prison-libya'>France 24</a>)</li><li>French judiciary: The Paris court will set the date and location for Sarkozy’s imprisonment following his five-year sentence. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/france/article/2025/10/13/sarkozy-to-learn-start-date-of-prison-term_6746363_7.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>French justice system: Imprisonment scheduling proceeds despite the appeal having been filed. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3328731/french-ex-president-sarkozy-will-serve-prison-time-despite-appeal-libya-funding-case'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/former-french-president-nicolas-sarkozy-to-learn-start-date-of-jail-term/article70157189.ece'>Former French President Nicolas Sarkozy to learn start date of jail term</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/france/20251013-france-ex-president-sarkozy-prison-libya'>France’s Sarkozy to learn prison date after five-year sentence over Libya campaign funds</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/france/article/2025/10/13/sarkozy-to-learn-start-date-of-prison-term_6746363_7.html'>Sarkozy to learn start date of prison term</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/french-president-nicolas-sarkozy-learn-prison-date-location-126461708'>Ex-French President Nicolas Sarkozy to learn prison date and location</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3328731/french-ex-president-sarkozy-will-serve-prison-time-despite-appeal-libya-funding-case'>French ex-leader Sarkozy to serve jail time despite appeal in Libya funding case</a> - scmp.com</li></ul>